HEADWORD: Firefish
<hw>Fire"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A singular marine fish of the genus <gen>Pterois</gen>, family
<fam>Scorp⟦ae⟧nid⟦ae⟧</fam>, of several species, inhabiting the
Indo-Pacific region. They are usually red, and have very large spinose
pectoral and dorsal fins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fireflaire</ent>⟦br⟧
